name: Oilers
summary: The Edmonton Oilers have forced a Game 7 in the Stanley Cup Final by defeating the Florida Panthers in Game 4 by a score of 8-1 and in Game 5 by a score of 5-1. Despite being on the brink of being swept, the Oilers fought back to win both games at home and push the series to a decisive Game 7. The Oilers, led by Connor McDavid, are now facing immense pressure to win Game 7 and claim their first Stanley Cup since 1990. Meanwhile, the Panthers, who once held a 3-1 series lead, must overcome the disappointment of losing two straight games and find a way to close out the series in Edmonton. The upcoming Game 7 promises to be a thrilling and historic matchup, with both teams determined to emerge victorious and lift the coveted Stanley Cup trophy.

name: Peru vs Chile
summary: Peru and Chile played out a goalless draw in their Copa America opener, with goalkeepers Claudio Bravo and Paolo Guerrero making history in the process. The draw means that Bravo has now kept the most clean sheets in Copa America history, while Guerrero has now scored the most goals in the tournament. The match was a cagey affair, with both teams struggling to create clear-cut chances. Peru had the better of the first half, but Chile improved after the break and had the best chance of the game when Alexis Sanchez hit the crossbar. In the end, both teams had to settle for a point, which leaves them both in a strong position to qualify from Group A.

summary: Taylor Wily, best known for his roles in "Hawaii Five-0" and "Forgetting Sarah Marshall," has passed away at the age of 56. The cause of his death has not been disclosed at this time. Wily played Kamekona Tupuola on "Hawaii Five-0," a role that made him a fan favorite. He also had a minor role in the 2008 film "Forgetting Sarah Marshall." Tributes and condolences from Wily's colleagues and fans have poured in on social media, expressing their sorrow and celebrating his life and work.

name: Peso Pluma
summary: Recently, Peso Pluma has released a dual album titled "Éxodo," which marks a departure from his typical corrido style. The album features a collaboration with rap star Cardi B on the track "Put Em in the Fridge," showcasing Peso Pluma's ability to blend Spanglish lyrics. Critics have praised his willingness to experiment, noting the bilingual bars and exploration of new genres. Despite controversy surrounding his music, Peso Pluma remains dedicated to promoting corridos and expanding its reach. His new album "Éxodo" is garnering attention and is featured in various publications' lists of noteworthy albums. Additionally, Peso Pluma is embarking on a tour and has collaborated with other artists, such as Ivan Cornejo, further solidifying his position in the music industry.
